President Muhammadu Buhari on Friday presented the All Progressives Congress flag to the party’s candidate in the upcoming Edo governorship election, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu.  The presentation of the party’s flag was done during Ize-Iyamu’s visit to the State House Abuja.  The Edo APC governorship candidate was accompanied by the Chairman of the party’s Caretaker Committee, Governor Mai Malm Buni of Yobe; Kano State Governor, Alhaji Abdullahi Ganduje; and Chairman of APC Governors’ Forum, Governor Atiku Bagudu Abubakar of Kebbi State.  The Presentation was also witnessed by the Chief of Staff to the President, Prof Ibrahim Gambari; and Senior Special Assistant to the President on Social Investment, Barrister Ishamel Ahmed.  Vice President Yemi Osinbajo later received the  Edo APC candidate and the team from the national headquarters in audience at the State House. Here are images of the presentation.        